I'd like to have all the filtering logic in a single method because it will make both the directory-walking logic and the filtering logic clearer (and easier to test) if they are separate. I'm anticipating that we may need to add different filters for other component types in the future, and that will be cleanest if things are sufficiently decoupled that we can delegate the logic for each component to a different class.

I also think it's going to be hard to make this work using regular expressions on Windows which uses a backslash as a path separator. How about something like this:

    for root, dirs, files in os.walk("."):
        root_parts = root.split(os.sep)[1:]
        for f in files:
            parts = root_parts + f.split(os.sep)
            if not self._include_file(parts):
                continue
            self._write_zip_file(zipf, root, f)

And then `_include_file` can work with a list of path segments rather than a string.

